**Our Strategic Approach:** Be the tutorial that teaches rather than instructs. Cover both routes (gel + lamp; regular polish + no lamp). Name the failure points explicitly. Explain coat-count logic. Give the DIY mixing ratio. Make the reader feel they've genuinely learned a skill, not followed a list.

